    "department": "Product ",
    "description": "At Nivoda https://nivoda.com/about, we’re reimagining how the world buys and sells jewellery. Our global marketplace connects retailers and suppliers across diamonds, gemstones, and finished jewellery - already powering over $300M in annual transactions and scaling fast toward our billion-dollar vision.\n\nWe’re bringing tech, data, and automation to a $350B industry that’s barely scratched the surface of digital transformation. The result? Explosive growth and massive opportunity powered by a team that makes it happen.\n\n\nOur Mission 💎\n\n\nThe idea of Nivoda was inspired by the ongoing inefficiency of diamond trading. We set out to develop the solution to help businesses, regardless of their size or location, increase their sales and margins, whilst removing the operational burden of sourcing diamonds.\n\n\nAbout the role ⭐️\nWe are looking for a data-driven and commercially minded Product Manager, Growth to join our Growth team. In this role, you will own the full growth funnel from user acquisition and activation through to retention and revenue expansion and will use experimentation, analytics, and cross-functional collaboration to drive measurable business impact.\n\nThis is a high-visibility role that sits at the intersection of product, marketing, engineering, and data. You will work closely with a cross-functional pod to design, prioritize, and execute growth initiatives that compound over time and move the needle on our core business metrics.\n\n\nWhat will you be doing? 🤔\n\nGrowth Strategy \u0026 Execution\n\n - Define and own the growth roadmap across acquisition, activation, retention, and monetization (AARRM) in alignment with company goals.\n\n - Identify growth opportunities by analyzing the full user funnel and pinpointing bottlenecks, drop-offs, and high-leverage levers.\n\n - Build and maintain a prioritized backlog of growth experiments, ensuring systematic testing and iteration.\n\nExperimentation \u0026 Analytics\n\n - Design, launch, and analyze A/B tests and multivariate experiments to validate growth hypotheses.\n\n - Translate quantitative data and qualitative user research into actionable product decisions.\n\n - Define, track, and report on key growth KPIs (e.g. activation rate, DAU/MAU, retention curves, conversion rates, LTV/CAC).\n\nProduct Development\n\n - Partner with engineering, design, and data teams to scope, build, and ship growth-focused features (e.g. onboarding flows, referral programs, upsell prompts, lifecycle nudges).\n\n - Optimize in-product experiences that drive user activation and reduce time-to-value.\n\n - Work with marketing to align product touchpoints with go-to-market campaigns and lifecycle communications.\n\nCross-functional Collaboration\n\n - Serve as the connective tissue between the Growth team and core product, marketing, sales, and data teams.\n\n - Present growth strategies, experiment results, and roadmap priorities to senior stakeholders.\n\n - Contribute to a culture of experimentation and continuous learning across the organization.\n\n\nWhat do we need from you? 😎\n\n\n - 3–6 years of experience in product management, growth marketing, or a related field, with a proven track record of driving measurable growth outcomes.\n\n - Strong analytical skills — comfortable working with SQL, product analytics tools (e.g. Amplitude, Mixpanel), and experimentation platforms (e.g. Optimizely, LaunchDarkly).\n\n - Deep understanding of the growth funnel and experience optimizing at least two stages (e.g. acquisition + activation, or activation + retention).\n\n - Experience designing and running A/B tests with statistical rigor.\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills; ability to synthesize complex data into clear narratives for diverse audiences.\n\n - Collaborative, low-ego working style with the ability to influence without authority.\n\nNice to Have\n\n - Experience in a SaaS, marketplace, or consumer tech environment.\n\n - Familiarity with product-led growth (PLG) models.\n\n - Exposure to CRM and lifecycle marketing tools (e.g. Braze, Intercom, Customer.io http://Customer.io).\n\n - Background in growth marketing, data science, or business analytics.\n\n - Experience working in an agile/scrum environment.\n\n\nOur culture and what we offer 😉\n\nAt Nivoda, we believe that employees today want to evolve in a collaborative, high-growth environment where they can demonstrate their abilities and thrive both professionally and personally. We are convinced that employees need to find alignment between their inner values and their company’s culture and mission to unlock their full potential. We work to create a culture of empowerment, continuous learning and growth where everyone can bring expertise, own projects and easily measure their impact.\n\nDynamic working environment in a rapidly growing company.\nEnjoy a pleasant, low-hierarchy work environment.\nEngage in intellectually challenging work that contributes significantly to Nivoda’s success and scalability.\n\nOur benefits\n\n\n🕰️ Flexible working hours and a vibrant company culture\n💻 Remote work\n🧠 Plenty of opportunities for growth and learning\n🏖️ Unlimited holiday allowance\n🚀 Chance to join and contribute to a company during its exponential expansion phase\n\n\nNivoda is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace dedicated to promoting diversity. We don’t discriminate on the basis of race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status or disability status.\nEven if it seems you don't meet 100% of our musts don't let it stop you, we are all about finding the best talent out there! Skills can be learned, and embracing diversity is invaluable.\n\nPlease note: Our Talent Acquisition Team is international coming from across the world. We kindly ask you to please submit your CV and application in English so that it can be reviewed correctly.\n\n*If after reading this job description you believe this is not the best fit for you, we’d encourage you to join our Talent Pool so we can keep you in mind as new roles open up.\nYou can sign up here: Nivoda Talent Pool https://nivoda.com/careers?ashby_jid=384ab7fa-bcf9-45ab-8665-f5ee26476804\n\nThis ensures you're among the first to hear about openings aligned with your skills and interests.",
